Subject: A Message to Liquidity Investors
To: <adam@marash.net>


Hello Adam,

As a valued investor in our initial Liquidity fund, we are delighted to
extend an invitation for you to participate in the newly-launched Liquidity
7 Fund.

Liquidity Group, an AI-based assessment management firm with headquarters
in Abu Dhabi and Tel Aviv, specializes in developing AI technologies for
financial applications and manages credit and equity investments with a
total AUM of $2.5 billion, consisting of $2 billion in venture debt funds
and $0.5 billion in equity investments.

In collaboration with Harel Insurance Group, Liquidity Group recently
announced the launch of a new $200m debt fund named =E2=80=9CLiquidity 7=E2=
=80=9D. This
fund is managed by a subsidiary of Liquidity Group and is regulated by the
Commission for the Supervision of the Financial Sector (CSSF) in Luxembourg=
.

With five additional debt funds, collectively managing over $2 billion, we
are now, for the first time since 2019, exclusively offering our qualified
Liquidity fund investors the opportunity to leverage their experience and
join the new Liquidity 7 fund, alongside premier institutional investors.

You can read more about Harel=E2=80=99s decision to join Liquidity 7 in thi=
s
recently-published Calcalist article
<https://liquidity-capital.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D43319ffd4a5=
b08608500979da&id=3D33d08fe04c&e=3Dfaa1ad9407>
.

The newly established Fund, managed by Liquidity Group, is set to invest in
growth-stage technology companies across Asia Pacific, the USA, and Europe.
It will operate in conjunction with other debt funds and investment
vehicles under Liquidity Group's management. The Fund's management company
holds a license that specifically allows it to provide commercial loans to
companies in Germany. This is significant as Germany represents a highly
regulated market with strong demand, where operating as a lender requires
specific licensing.

Investments will be conducted utilizing Liquidity=E2=80=99s advanced propri=
etary
risk prediction technology. This technology has been instrumental in
Liquidity Group's remarkable success in the credit sector, even amidst
global market uncertainties and major macro events like war and the
COVID-19 pandemic.

The Fund is a key component of Liquidity Group's broader strategy that
leverages advanced AI and patented machine learning technologies for
effective capital allocation and management. In 2023, these technologies
significantly contributed to Liquidity Group's expansion. Notable
milestones included MUFG raising its investment commitment to $1 billion in
the debt funds, the creation of four new credit funds, and the launch of
Liquidity=E2=80=99s inaugural equity investment fund. This equity fund, wit=
h a
focus on technology companies and valued at $0.5 billion, was recently
established in Singapore in October 2023.

For more information and to register for access to the Fund, please follow =
this
<https://liquidity-capital.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D43319ffd4a5=
b08608500979da&id=3D76cfb76c3b&e=3Dfaa1ad9407>
link
<https://liquidity-capital.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D43319ffd4a5=
b08608500979da&id=3D0054747c27&e=3Dfaa1ad9407>
.
*Subscription is conditional on filling out a Qualified Investor
Declaration, in accordance with the provisions of the law.
